## hex1_AMD64_darwin.hex0 — hand-rolled hex0 source that assembles to a
## runnable Darwin Mach-O hex1-darwin binary.  Replaces
## scripts/stage0/phase1-amd64-hex1.pl entirely.
##
## Layout (file offsets):
##   0x000-0x3FF  Mach-O header (1024 bytes — 15 load commands).
##                Constants chosen for Darwin amd64 ABI: PAGEZERO,
##                __TEXT at 0x600000 size 0x800000, __DATA at 0xE00000
##                size 0x100000, __LINKEDIT at 0x1600000, entry 0x400.
##   0x400-0x5FB  Darwin-ported hex1 body, with all RIP-rel32 disps
##                baked for data_vm = 0xE00000, and the Linux read
##                pattern `31 C0 0F 05 48 85 C0 74 0B` replaced with
##                `E9 <disp32> 90 90 74 0B` so partial reads on Darwin
##                EINTR are retried via the stub.
##   0x5FC-0xDFC  Zero filler — required so the EINTR retry stub lands
##                at file offset 0xDFD (the jmp in the body targets it).
##   0xDFD-0xE0B  EINTR retry stub (15 bytes):
##                  B8 03 00 00 02   mov eax, 0x2000003 (Darwin read)
##                  0F 05            syscall
##                  48 85 C0         test rax, rax
##                  E9 8B F7 FF FF   jmp back to caller
##
## Build:  hex0 hex1_AMD64_darwin.hex0 hex1-darwin
##         dd if=/dev/zero of=hex1-darwin bs=1 count=1 seek=16777215 conv=notrunc
##         sign hex1-darwin
##
## Maintainer regenerates via scripts/stage0/regen-hex1-darwin.sh
## whenever upstream stage0Sources/AMD64/hex1_AMD64.hex0 changes.

